#!/usr/bin/env perl

use strict;
use warnings;
use App::Normalo;

our $VERSION = '0.02';

exit App::Normalo->run(@ARGV);

__END__

=encoding UTF-8

=head1 NAME

normalo - Normalize filenames to kebab-case

=head1 SYNOPSIS

B<normalo> [B<-h>|B<-v>] I<FILE>...

=head1 DESCRIPTION

B<normalo> normalizes filenames by converting them to kebab-case format.
It performs the following transformations:

=over 4

=item * Converts UTF-8 characters to ASCII equivalents (transliteration)

=item * Converts to lowercase

=item * Replaces spaces, underscores, dots, and control characters with hyphens

=item * Removes non-alphanumeric characters (except hyphens)

=item * Collapses multiple consecutive hyphens into a single hyphen

=item * Preserves file extensions

=back

=head1 OPTIONS

=over 4

=item B<-h>, B<--help>

Display help message and exit.

=item B<-v>, B<--version>

Display version information and exit.

=back

=head1 EXAMPLES

  normalo "My File.txt"
  # Renames to: my-file.txt

  normalo file1.txt file2.txt file3.txt
  # Renames multiple files

  normalo "Caf√©_2024 (Final).PDF"
  # Renames to: cafe-2024-final.pdf

=head1 DIAGNOSTICS

=over 4

=item C<< %s is not a regular file >>

The specified path is not a regular file. Only regular files can be renamed.

=item C<< Failed to rename %s to %s: %s >>

The rename operation failed. The error message from the system is included.

=item C<< missing file operand >>

No files were specified on the command line.

=back

=head1 EXIT STATUS

The B<normalo> utility exits 0 on success, and 1 if an error occurs.

